cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning approach to solve the cache-enabled QoE-driven video rate allocation problem. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on video streaming over wireless networks and proposes a solution to maintain high-quality user experience of mobile users moving among small cells. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with video streaming and proposes a solution to allocate video rates dynamically. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper establishes a mathematical model for the cache-enabled QoE-driven video rate allocation problem. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a control algorithm to allocate video rates dynamically and maintain high-quality user experience.
